items.title: Path to the Postseason: Sept. 12
items.summary: The 5-3 win over the Giants punched the Dodgers' ticket to the postseason, guaranteeing them at least a Wild Card spot as they chase a sixth-consecutive National League West title.
items.content: The 5-3 win over the Giants punched the Dodgers' ticket to the postseason, guaranteeing them at least a Wild Card spot as they chase a sixth-consecutive National League West title.

items.title: Rockies' Gray avoids trouble in 10-K gem
items.summary: It was as if the D-backs runners who occupied each base with no outs in the third inning were invisible to Rockies righty starter Jon Gray. If he could find his groove, he figured, no one could hurt him.

items.title: Angels 'thrilled' with Richards' home return
items.summary: It had been 17 months since Garrett Richards had taken the mound at Angel Stadium, but he enjoyed a homecoming of sorts on Tuesday night, tossing five innings of one-run ball in the Angels' 1-0 series-opening loss to the Astros.
